[30;1m96 | [0m[35mHighlights of this release:[0m
[30;1m97 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m98 | [0m[35m1. Experimental perform_rs and perform_rb methods have been added to Curl[0m
[30;1m99 | [0m[35m   objects. They return response body as a string and a byte string,[0m
[30;1m100 | [0m[35m   respectively. The goal of these methods is to improve PycURL's usability[0m
[30;1m101 | [0m[35m   for typical use cases, specifically removing the need to set up[0m
[30;1m102 | [0m[35m   StringIO/BytesIO objects to store the response body.[0m

[30;1m1 | [0m[35msetopt(option, value) -> None[0m
[30;1m2 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m3 | [0m[35mSet curl multi option. Corresponds to `curl_multi_setopt`_ in libcurl.[0m
[30;1m4 | [0m[35m[0m
